{"id":"ukpds","version":"0.0.2","templates":[{"id":"ukpds","version":"0.1.0"}],"language":"en","updated":"2021-09-01T10:10:51+02:00","authors":[{"name":"Rosario Silva Sepulveda","email":"rosario.sepulveda@cambio.se"}],"format":"CambioForm.v1","name":"ukpds","actions":[{"assignments":["male_age.hidden=false","male_age.required=true"],"condition":"gender.value=='at0005'","otherwise":["male_age.hidden=true","male_age.required=false"]},{"condition":"gender.value=='at0006'","assignments":["female_age.hidden=false","female_age.required=true"],"otherwise":["female_age.hidden=true","female_age.required=false"]}],"guidelines":[{"condition":"(female_age || male_age) && diabetes_duration && smoking_status && hba1c && systolic_bp && 'total_cholesterol_hdl' && microalbumin","execution":[{"id":"ukpds","version":"1"}]}],"elements":[{"type":"form","children":[{"type":"container","children":[{"type":"row","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"children":[{"type":"column","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"children":[{"text":"## United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study (UKPDS) Coronary Risk Estimator\n\nThe estimator assesses eight parameters related to the probability of developing Coronary Heart Disease (CHD) when diagnosed with type 2 diabetes mellitus:\n\n\n\n- age, \n- gender, \n- diabetes duration in years, \n- smoking status, \n- hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c) level, \n- systolic blood pressure, \n- total cholesterol to high-density lipoprotein cholesterol ratio, and \n- microalbumin in urine. \n\n\n\nEach parameter's value is added and the total score is interpreted as\n\n\n\n- Average Risk (0-17): <15% probability of having CHD in the next 10 years,\n- Elevated Risk (18-31): 15-30% probability of having CHD in the next 10 years,\n- High Risk (32-69): >30% probability of having CHD in the next 10 years.","type":"text","size":"m","position":"left"}]}]},{"type":"row","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"type":"column